GoalDesc: Ensure healthy lives and promote well-being for all at all ages
TargetDesc: By 2030, ensure universal access to sexual and reproductive health-care services, including for family planning, information and education, and the integration of reproductive health into national strategies and programmes
IndicatorDesc: Proportion of women of reproductive age (aged 15-49 years) who have their need for family planning satisfied with modern methods
SeriesDesc: Proportion of women married or in a union of reproductive age (aged 15-49 years) who have their need for family planning satisfied with modern methods (% of women aged 15-49 years)
Source: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division. Model-based Estimates and Projections of Family Planning Indicators 2018. New York: United Nations.
Footnotes: The global indicator is intended to represent all women of reproductive age. Given current data limitations, the model-based estimates represent women who are married or in a union.

Source: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division. Model-based Estimates and Projections of Family Planning Indicators 2018. New York: United Nations.
